
[1]indigo

   IN'DIGO, n. [L. indicum, from India.] A substance or dye, prepared from
   the leaves and stalks of the indigo-plant, which are steeped in water
   till the pulp is extracted, when the tincture is drawn off and churned
   or agitated,till the dye begins to granulate. The flakes are then left
   to settle; the liquor is drawn off,and the indigo is drained in bags
   and dried in boxes. It is used for dyeing blue.
